case_circumstances: The body of a young African American male was found floating in the Columbia River near the Rose City Yacht club on April 25, 1992.  The man had been deceased for at least several weeks if not several months.  He was wearing distinctive clothing and jewelry, please see clothing and accessories tab for details.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_on_body:
"BUGLE BOY" sweatshirt, black in color, size Large
"NIKE" T-shirt, white in color.
"LEVI" denim shorts, size 33 waist
white athletic socks
case_jewelry:
Yellow-faced Mickey Mouse watch, Disney brand with a black plastic band
Black belt with silver decoration
woven metal neck chain, gold-colored
case_other_items_with_body:
Several keys on rings in his pocket: Scorpio keychain, U.S. Marine Corp keychain and two metal disks that are embossed with a "36" and a "33". 
Key chain also has a plastic thunderbird, turquoise in color, attached to it.
Disks may be related to tokens issued to labor union members, or longshoremen union members.
dental: Dental information / charting is currently not available
documents: There are currently no documents available for this case.
